-- Qatar's Tasweeq Sells Deodorized Field Condensate for Loading in January
-- B y   C h r i s t i a n   S c h m o l l i n g e r
-- 2010-11-12T06:40:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-12/qatar-s-tasweeq-sells-deodorized-field-condensate-for-january.html
Qatar International Petroleum
Marketing Co., or Tasweeq, sold 2 million barrels of deodorized
field condensate for loading in January, according to four
traders who participate in the market.  Exxon Mobil Corp., Chevron Corp., Mitsubishi Corp. and JX-
Nippon Holdings Inc. purchased the shipments, the traders said.  Details of the deal are as follows:  Condensate is a type of light crude oil produced in
association with natural gas and is usually processed into fuel
products such as diesel and  naphtha , a raw material for gasoline
and chemicals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
